26// Return the number of elements of a packed enum, including the InvalidEnum element.
27template <typename E>
28constexpr size_t EnumSize()
29{
30 using UnderlyingType = typename std::underlying_type<E>::type;
31 return static_cast<UnderlyingType>(E::EnumCount);
32}
33
34// Implementation of AllEnums which allows iterating over all the possible values for a packed enums
35// like so:
36// for (auto value : AllEnums<MyPackedEnum>()) {
37// // Do something with the enum.
38// }
39
40template <typename E>
41class EnumIterator final
42{
43 private:
44 using UnderlyingType = typename std::underlying_type<E>::type;
45
46 public:
47 EnumIterator(E value) : mValue(static_cast<UnderlyingType>(value)) {}
48 EnumIterator &operator++()
49 {
50 mValue++;
51 return *this;
52 }
53 bool operator==(const EnumIterator &other) const { return mValue == other.mValue; }
54 bool operator!=(const EnumIterator &other) const { return mValue != other.mValue; }
55 E operator*() const { return static_cast<E>(mValue); }
56
57 private:
58 UnderlyingType mValue;
59};
60
61template <typename E>
62struct AllEnums
63{
64 EnumIterator<E> begin() const { return {static_cast<E>(0)}; }
65 EnumIterator<E> end() const { return {E::InvalidEnum}; }
66};
67
68// PackedEnumMap<E, T> is like an std::array<T, E::EnumCount> but is indexed with enum values. It
69// implements all of the std::array interface except with enum values instead of indices.
70template <typename E, typename T, size_t MaxSize = EnumSize<E>()>
71class PackedEnumMap
72{
73 using UnderlyingType = typename std::underlying_type<E>::type;
74 using Storage = std::array<T, MaxSize>;
75
76 public:
77 using InitPair = std::pair<E, T>;
78
79 constexpr PackedEnumMap() = default;
80
81 constexpr PackedEnumMap(std::initializer_list<InitPair> init) : mPrivateData{}
82 {
83 // We use a for loop instead of range-for to work around a limitation in MSVC.
84 for (const InitPair *it = init.begin(); it != init.end(); ++it)
85 {
86#if (__cplusplus < 201703L)
87 // This horrible const_cast pattern is necessary to work around a constexpr limitation.
88 // See https://stackoverflow.com/q/34199774/ . Note that it should be fixed with C++17.
89 const_cast<T &>(const_cast<const Storage &>(
90 mPrivateData)[static_cast<UnderlyingType>(it->first)]) = it->second;
91#else
92 mPrivateData[static_cast<UnderlyingType>(it->first)] = it->second;
93#endif
94 }
95 }
96
97 // types:
98 using value_type = T;
99 using pointer = T *;
100 using const_pointer = const T *;
101 using reference = T &;
102 using const_reference = const T &;
103
104 using size_type = size_t;
105 using difference_type = ptrdiff_t;
106
107 using iterator = typename Storage::iterator;
108 using const_iterator = typename Storage::const_iterator;
109 using reverse_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<iterator>;
110 using const_reverse_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<const_iterator>;
111
112 // No explicit construct/copy/destroy for aggregate type
113 void fill(const T &u) { mPrivateData.fill(u); }
114 void swap(PackedEnumMap<E, T, MaxSize> &a) noexcept { mPrivateData.swap(a.mPrivateData); }
115
116 // iterators:
117 iterator begin() noexcept { return mPrivateData.begin(); }
118 const_iterator begin() const noexcept { return mPrivateData.begin(); }
119 iterator end() noexcept { return mPrivateData.end(); }
120 const_iterator end() const noexcept { return mPrivateData.end(); }
121
122 reverse_iterator rbegin() noexcept { return mPrivateData.rbegin(); }
123 const_reverse_iterator rbegin() const noexcept { return mPrivateData.rbegin(); }
124 reverse_iterator rend() noexcept { return mPrivateData.rend(); }
125 const_reverse_iterator rend() const noexcept { return mPrivateData.rend(); }
126
127 // capacity:
128 constexpr size_type size() const noexcept { return mPrivateData.size(); }
129 constexpr size_type max_size() const noexcept { return mPrivateData.max_size(); }
130 constexpr bool empty() const noexcept { return mPrivateData.empty(); }
131
132 // element access:
133 reference operator[](E n)
134 {
135 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(n) < mPrivateData.size());
136 return mPrivateData[static_cast<UnderlyingType>(n)];
137 }
138
139 constexpr const_reference operator[](E n) const
140 {
141 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(n) < mPrivateData.size());
142 return mPrivateData[static_cast<UnderlyingType>(n)];
143 }
144
145 const_reference at(E n) const { return mPrivateData.at(static_cast<UnderlyingType>(n)); }
146 reference at(E n) { return mPrivateData.at(static_cast<UnderlyingType>(n)); }
147
148 reference front() { return mPrivateData.front(); }
149 const_reference front() const { return mPrivateData.front(); }
150 reference back() { return mPrivateData.back(); }
151 const_reference back() const { return mPrivateData.back(); }
152
153 T *data() noexcept { return mPrivateData.data(); }
154 const T *data() const noexcept { return mPrivateData.data(); }
155
156 bool operator==(const PackedEnumMap &rhs) const { return mPrivateData == rhs.mPrivateData; }
157 bool operator!=(const PackedEnumMap &rhs) const { return mPrivateData != rhs.mPrivateData; }
158
159 private:
160 Storage mPrivateData;
161};
162
163// PackedEnumBitSetE> is like an std::bitset<E::EnumCount> but is indexed with enum values. It
164// implements the std::bitset interface except with enum values instead of indices.
165template <typename E, typename DataT = uint32_t>
166using PackedEnumBitSet = BitSetT<EnumSize<E>(), DataT, E>;

228enum class PrimitiveMode : uint8_t
229{
230 Points = 0x0,
231 Lines = 0x1,
232 LineLoop = 0x2,
233 LineStrip = 0x3,
234 Triangles = 0x4,
235 TriangleStrip = 0x5,
236 TriangleFan = 0x6,
237 Unused1 = 0x7,
238 Unused2 = 0x8,
239 Unused3 = 0x9,
240 LinesAdjacency = 0xA,
241 LineStripAdjacency = 0xB,
242 TrianglesAdjacency = 0xC,
243 TriangleStripAdjacency = 0xD,
244
245 InvalidEnum = 0xE,
246 EnumCount = 0xE,
247};
248
249template <>
250constexpr PrimitiveMode FromGLenum<PrimitiveMode>(GLenum from)
251{
252 if (from >= static_cast<GLenum>(PrimitiveMode::EnumCount))
253 {
254 return PrimitiveMode::InvalidEnum;
255 }
256
257 return static_cast<PrimitiveMode>(from);
258}
259
260constexpr GLenum ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode from)
261{
262 return static_cast<GLenum>(from);
263}
264
265static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::Points) == GL_POINTS, "PrimitiveMode violation");
266static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::Lines) == GL_LINES, "PrimitiveMode violation");
267static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::LineLoop) == GL_LINE_LOOP, "PrimitiveMode violation");
268static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::LineStrip) == GL_LINE_STRIP, "PrimitiveMode violation");
269static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::Triangles) == GL_TRIANGLES, "PrimitiveMode violation");
270static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::TriangleStrip) == GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP,
271 "PrimitiveMode violation");
272static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan) == GL_TRIANGLE_FAN, "PrimitiveMode violation");
273static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::LinesAdjacency) == GL_LINES_ADJACENCY,
274 "PrimitiveMode violation");
275static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::LineStripAdjacency) == GL_LINE_STRIP_ADJACENCY,
276 "PrimitiveMode violation");
277static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::TrianglesAdjacency) == GL_TRIANGLES_ADJACENCY,
278 "PrimitiveMode violation");
279static_assert(ToGLenum(PrimitiveMode::TriangleStripAdjacency) == GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP_ADJACENCY,
280 "PrimitiveMode violation");

284enum class DrawElementsType : size_t
285{
286 UnsignedByte = 0,
287 UnsignedShort = 1,
288 UnsignedInt = 2,
289 InvalidEnum = 3,
290 EnumCount = 3,
291};
292
293template <>
294constexpr DrawElementsType FromGLenum<DrawElementsType>(GLenum from)
295{
296
297 GLenum scaled = (from - GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE);
298 // This code sequence generates a ROR instruction on x86/arm. We want to check if the lowest bit
299 // of scaled is set and if (scaled >> 1) is greater than a non-pot value. If we rotate the
300 // lowest bit to the hightest bit both conditions can be checked with a single test.
301 static_assert(sizeof(GLenum) == 4, "Update (scaled << 31) to sizeof(GLenum) * 8 - 1");
302 GLenum packed = (scaled >> 1) | (scaled << 31);
303
304 // operator ? with a simple assignment usually translates to a cmov instruction and thus avoids
305 // a branch.
306 packed = (packed >= static_cast<GLenum>(DrawElementsType::EnumCount))
307 ? static_cast<GLenum>(DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum)
308 : packed;
309
310 return static_cast<DrawElementsType>(packed);
311}
312
313constexpr GLenum ToGLenum(DrawElementsType from)
314{
315 return ((static_cast<GLenum>(from) << 1) + GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE);
316}
317
318#define ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(type, packed, glenum) \
319 static_assert(ToGLenum(type::packed) == glenum, #type " violation"); \
320 static_assert(FromGLenum<type>(glenum) == type::packed, #type " violation")
321
322ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(DrawElementsType, UnsignedByte, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE);
323ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(DrawElementsType, UnsignedShort, GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT);
324ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(DrawElementsType, UnsignedInt, GL_UNSIGNED_INT);
325
326std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &os, DrawElementsType value);

328enum class BlendEquationType
329{
330 Add = 0, // GLenum == 0x8006
331 Min = 1, // GLenum == 0x8007
332 Max = 2, // GLenum == 0x8008
333 Unused = 3,
334 Subtract = 4, // GLenum == 0x800A
335 ReverseSubtract = 5, // GLenum == 0x800B
336 InvalidEnum = 6,
337 EnumCount = 6
338};
339
340template <>
341constexpr BlendEquationType FromGLenum<BlendEquationType>(GLenum from)
342{
343 const GLenum scaled = (from - GL_FUNC_ADD);
344 return (scaled == static_cast<GLenum>(BlendEquationType::Unused) ||
345 scaled >= static_cast<GLenum>(BlendEquationType::EnumCount))
346 ? BlendEquationType::InvalidEnum
347 : static_cast<BlendEquationType>(scaled);
348}
349
350constexpr GLenum ToGLenum(BlendEquationType from)
351{
352 return static_cast<GLenum>(from) + GL_FUNC_ADD;
353}
354
355ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(BlendEquationType, Add, GL_FUNC_ADD);
356ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(BlendEquationType, Min, GL_MIN);
357ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(BlendEquationType, Max, GL_MAX);
358ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(BlendEquationType, Subtract, GL_FUNC_SUBTRACT);
359ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(BlendEquationType, ReverseSubtract, GL_FUNC_REVERSE_SUBTRACT);
360
361std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &os, BlendEquationType value);

363enum class BlendFactorType
364{
365 Zero = 0, // GLenum == 0
366 One = 1, // GLenum == 1
367
368 MinSrcDstType = 2,
369 SrcColor = 2, // GLenum == 0x0300
370 OneMinusSrcColor = 3, // GLenum == 0x0301
371 SrcAlpha = 4, // GLenum == 0x0302
372 OneMinusSrcAlpha = 5, // GLenum == 0x0303
373 DstAlpha = 6, // GLenum == 0x0304
374 OneMinusDstAlpha = 7, // GLenum == 0x0305
375 DstColor = 8, // GLenum == 0x0306
376 OneMinusDstColor = 9, // GLenum == 0x0307
377 SrcAlphaSaturate = 10, // GLenum == 0x0308
378 MaxSrcDstType = 10,
379
380 MinConstantType = 11,
381 ConstantColor = 11, // GLenum == 0x8001
382 OneMinusConstantColor = 12, // GLenum == 0x8002
383 ConstantAlpha = 13, // GLenum == 0x8003
384 OneMinusConstantAlpha = 14, // GLenum == 0x8004
385 MaxConstantType = 14,
386
387 // GL_EXT_blend_func_extended
388
389 Src1Alpha = 15, // GLenum == 0x8589
390
391 Src1Color = 16, // GLenum == 0x88F9
392 OneMinusSrc1Color = 17, // GLenum == 0x88FA
393 OneMinusSrc1Alpha = 18, // GLenum == 0x88FB
394
395 InvalidEnum = 19,
396 EnumCount = 19
397};
398
399template <>
400constexpr BlendFactorType FromGLenum<BlendFactorType>(GLenum from)
401{
402 if (from <= 1)
403 return static_cast<BlendFactorType>(from);
404 if (from >= GL_SRC_COLOR && from <= GL_SRC_ALPHA_SATURATE)
405 return static_cast<BlendFactorType>(from - GL_SRC_COLOR + 2);
406 if (from >= GL_CONSTANT_COLOR && from <= GL_ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_ALPHA)
407 return static_cast<BlendFactorType>(from - GL_CONSTANT_COLOR + 11);
408 if (from == GL_SRC1_ALPHA_EXT)
409 return BlendFactorType::Src1Alpha;
410 if (from >= GL_SRC1_COLOR_EXT && from <= GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC1_ALPHA_EXT)
411 return static_cast<BlendFactorType>(from - GL_SRC1_COLOR_EXT + 16);
412 return BlendFactorType::InvalidEnum;
413}
414
415constexpr GLenum ToGLenum(BlendFactorType from)
416{
417 const GLenum value = static_cast<GLenum>(from);
418 if (value <= 1)
419 return value;
420 if (from >= BlendFactorType::MinSrcDstType && from <= BlendFactorType::MaxSrcDstType)
421 return value - 2 + GL_SRC_COLOR;
422 if (from >= BlendFactorType::MinConstantType && from <= BlendFactorType::MaxConstantType)
423 return value - 11 + GL_CONSTANT_COLOR;
424 if (from == BlendFactorType::Src1Alpha)
425 return GL_SRC1_ALPHA_EXT;
426 return value - 16 + GL_SRC1_COLOR_EXT;
427}

430ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(BlendFactorType, One, GL_ONE);
431ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(BlendFactorType, SrcColor, GL_SRC_COLOR);
432ANGLE_VALIDATE_PACKED_ENUM(BlendFactorType, OneMinusSrcColor, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR);

451enum class VertexAttribType
452{
453 Byte = 0, // GLenum == 0x1400
454 UnsignedByte = 1, // GLenum == 0x1401
455 Short = 2, // GLenum == 0x1402
456 UnsignedShort = 3, // GLenum == 0x1403
457 Int = 4, // GLenum == 0x1404
458 UnsignedInt = 5, // GLenum == 0x1405
459 Float = 6, // GLenum == 0x1406
460 Unused1 = 7, // GLenum == 0x1407
461 Unused2 = 8, // GLenum == 0x1408
462 Unused3 = 9, // GLenum == 0x1409
463 Unused4 = 10, // GLenum == 0x140A
464 HalfFloat = 11, // GLenum == 0x140B
465 Fixed = 12, // GLenum == 0x140C
466 MaxBasicType = 12,
467 UnsignedInt2101010 = 13, // GLenum == 0x8368
468 HalfFloatOES = 14, // GLenum == 0x8D61
469 Int2101010 = 15, // GLenum == 0x8D9F
470 UnsignedInt1010102 = 16, // GLenum == 0x8DF6
471 Int1010102 = 17, // GLenum == 0x8DF7
472 InvalidEnum = 18,
473 EnumCount = 18,
474};
475
476template <>
477constexpr VertexAttribType FromGLenum<VertexAttribType>(GLenum from)
478{
479 GLenum packed = from - GL_BYTE;
480 if (packed <= static_cast<GLenum>(VertexAttribType::MaxBasicType))
481 return static_cast<VertexAttribType>(packed);
482 if (from == GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV)
483 return VertexAttribType::UnsignedInt2101010;
484 if (from == GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES)
485 return VertexAttribType::HalfFloatOES;
486 if (from == GL_INT_2_10_10_10_REV)
487 return VertexAttribType::Int2101010;
488 if (from == GL_UNSIGNED_INT_10_10_10_2_OES)
489 return VertexAttribType::UnsignedInt1010102;
490 if (from == GL_INT_10_10_10_2_OES)
491 return VertexAttribType::Int1010102;
492 return VertexAttribType::InvalidEnum;
493}
494
495constexpr GLenum ToGLenum(VertexAttribType from)
496{
497 // This could be optimized using a constexpr table.
498 if (from == VertexAttribType::Int2101010)
499 return GL_INT_2_10_10_10_REV;
500 if (from == VertexAttribType::HalfFloatOES)
501 return GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES;
502 if (from == VertexAttribType::UnsignedInt2101010)
503 return GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV;
504 if (from == VertexAttribType::UnsignedInt1010102)
505 return GL_UNSIGNED_INT_10_10_10_2_OES;
506 if (from == VertexAttribType::Int1010102)
507 return GL_INT_10_10_10_2_OES;
508 return static_cast<GLenum>(from) + GL_BYTE;
509}

531struct ResourceTypeToID;

533template <typename T>
534struct IsResourceIDType;

536// Clang Format doesn't like the following X macro.
537// clang-format off
538#define ANGLE_ID_TYPES_OP(X) \
539 X(Buffer) \
540 X(FenceNV) \
541 X(Framebuffer) \
542 X(MemoryObject) \
543 X(Path) \
544 X(ProgramPipeline) \
545 X(Query) \
546 X(Renderbuffer) \
547 X(Sampler) \
548 X(Semaphore) \
549 X(Texture) \
550 X(TransformFeedback) \
551 X(VertexArray)
552// clang-format on
553
554#define ANGLE_DEFINE_ID_TYPE(Type) \
555 class Type; \
556 struct Type##ID \
557 { \
558 GLuint value; \
559 }; \
560 template <> \
561 struct ResourceTypeToID<Type> \
562 { \
563 using IDType = Type##ID; \
564 }; \
565 template <> \
566 struct IsResourceIDType<Type##ID> \
567 { \
568 static constexpr bool value = true; \
569 };
570
571ANGLE_ID_TYPES_OP(ANGLE_DEFINE_ID_TYPE)
572
573#undef ANGLE_DEFINE_ID_TYPE
574#undef ANGLE_ID_TYPES_OP

608template <typename T>
609struct IsResourceIDType
610{
611 static constexpr bool value = false;
612};

614template <typename T>
615bool ValueEquals(T lhs, T rhs)
616{
617 return lhs.value == rhs.value;
618}
619
620// Util funcs for resourceIDs
621template <typename T>
622typename std::enable_if<IsResourceIDType<T>::value, bool>::type operator==(const T &lhs,
623 const T &rhs)
624{
625 return lhs.value == rhs.value;
626}
627
628template <typename T>
629typename std::enable_if<IsResourceIDType<T>::value, bool>::type operator!=(const T &lhs,
630 const T &rhs)
631{
632 return lhs.value != rhs.value;
633}
634
635template <typename T>
636typename std::enable_if<IsResourceIDType<T>::value, bool>::type operator<(const T &lhs,
637 const T &rhs)
638{
639 return lhs.value < rhs.value;
640}

644GLuint GetIDValue(ResourceIDType id);

647inline GLuint GetIDValue(GLuint id)
648{

653inline GLuint GetIDValue(ResourceIDType id)

658// First case: handling packed enums.
659template <typename EnumT, typename FromT>
660typename std::enable_if<std::is_enum<EnumT>::value, EnumT>::type FromGL(FromT from)
661{
662 return FromGLenum<EnumT>(from);
663}
664
665// Second case: handling non-pointer resource ids.
666template <typename EnumT, typename FromT>
667typename std::enable_if<!std::is_pointer<FromT>::value && !std::is_enum<EnumT>::value, EnumT>::type
668FromGL(FromT from)
669{
670 return {from};
671}
672
673// Third case: handling pointer resource ids.
674template <typename EnumT, typename FromT>
675typename std::enable_if<std::is_pointer<FromT>::value && !std::is_enum<EnumT>::value, EnumT>::type
676FromGL(FromT from)
677{
678 return reinterpret_cast<EnumT>(from);
679}
